u - user
g - group
o- others


4 stands for read
2 stands for write
1 stands for execute
0 no permissons

7 stands for all permissions

the command to change permissions to the outside world
chmod o+w Filename
example:
chmod 754 Filename 
means 
users will have read write and execute
groups will have read and execute permissions
others have only have write access.
